    slug: "the-gift-of-eid",
    description: `The Gift of Eid is a beautifully illustrated children's book that introduces young readers to the significance, joy, and spiritual meaning of Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha. Published by Darussalam, this engaging storybook is designed to help children understand why Muslims celebrate these two major Islamic festivals and how each occasion carries deep religious importance beyond the festivities and celebrations. The narrative walks children through the journey of Ramadan leading up to Eid al-Fitr, explaining how the month of fasting culminates in a day of gratitude, charity, and communal prayer. It covers the essential acts of worship associated with Eid, including the special Eid prayer (Salat al-Eid), the giving of Zakat al-Fitr before the prayer, and the Sunnah practices recommended by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) such as wearing new clothes, eating something sweet before the prayer on Eid al-Fitr, and greeting fellow Muslims with warmth and joy. For Eid al-Adha, the book explains the story of Prophet Ibrahim (Abraham) and his willingness to sacrifice his son in obedience to Allah, connecting this historical event to the rituals of Hajj and the practice of Qurbani (sacrifice). Children learn about the spirit of sacrifice, trust in Allah, and the importance of sharing meat with family, friends, and those in need. The Gift of Eid also emphasizes the social dimensions of both festivals — visiting relatives, strengthening community bonds, giving gifts, and showing kindness to neighbours. Each page is filled with colourful illustrations that capture the excitement and warmth of Eid celebrations in Muslim households around the world. The language used throughout the book is simple and age-appropriate, making it suitable for children aged 4 to 10 years. Parents and teachers will find this book to be a valuable resource for teaching children about Islamic traditions in an engaging and memorable way. It serves as an excellent read-aloud book for bedtime storytelling or as part of an Islamic studies curriculum in schools and weekend madrasah programmes. By reading The Gift of Eid, children develop a strong emotional connection to their faith and a clear understanding of the values that underpin Islamic celebrations — gratitude, generosity, compassion, and devotion to Allah.`,
    metaDescription: "The Gift of Eid children's book teaches kids about Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha with colourful illustrations and Islamic values. Perfect for ages 4-10."
