    slug: "the-gift-of-jumuah",
    description: `The Gift of Jumuah is a comprehensive Islamic book that focuses on the virtues, rulings, and spiritual significance of Friday (Yawm al-Jumuah) in Islam. Categorised under Fiqh, this Darussalam publication provides readers with a thorough understanding of why Friday holds a special and elevated status among the days of the week in Islamic tradition, and how Muslims should prepare for and observe this blessed day in accordance with the Shariah. The book draws extensively from the Quran and authentic hadith collections to establish the importance of Jumuah, beginning with the Quranic injunction in Surah Al-Jumuah that calls upon believers to leave their trade and hasten to the remembrance of Allah when the call to Friday prayer is made. The author presents a detailed compilation of the virtues of Friday as narrated by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), including the hadith stating that Friday is the best day on which the sun rises, the day when Adam was created, the day he was admitted to Paradise, and the day on which the Day of Judgement will take place. The book covers the complete Fiqh of Jumuah prayer, including the conditions under which it becomes obligatory, the requirements for a valid Jumuah congregation, the role and qualifications of the Imam, the structure of the Khutbah (Friday sermon), and the proper etiquette of listening to the sermon. It addresses common questions and contemporary issues related to Jumuah such as the ruling for women attending Jumuah, travelling on Friday, the significance of reciting Surah Al-Kahf, and the recommended supplications and acts of worship specific to this day. The text also discusses the Sunnah practices associated with Friday, including performing ghusl (ritual bathing), wearing clean clothes, using perfume, arriving early at the mosque, and increasing supplications during the recommended hours. The Gift of Jumuah serves as both an educational resource and a practical guide for Muslims who wish to maximise the spiritual benefits of every Friday. It is particularly useful for Imams, Khateebs, Islamic studies teachers, and general readers who want to deepen their understanding of this weekly celebration of faith and community.`,
