    slug: "the-gift-of-my-mother",
    description: `The Gift of My Mother is a heartwarming Islamic book that celebrates the sacred bond between a mother and her children, highlighting the elevated status that Islam grants to mothers. Published under the Women's category by Darussalam, this book presents a comprehensive exploration of motherhood in Islamic teachings, drawing upon the Quran, the Prophetic tradition, and the exemplary lives of the Sahabiyat (female companions of the Prophet) to illustrate the profound respect, love, and care that Islam demands from children towards their mothers. The book opens by establishing the foundational Quranic verse that commands kindness to parents, with special emphasis on the mother's struggles during pregnancy, childbirth, and nursing, as described in Surah Luqman and Surah Al-Ahqaf. It presents the famous hadith in which a man asked Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who deserves the best companionship, and the Prophet replied "Your mother" three times before saying "your father," underscoring the mother's paramount right to good treatment. Readers will find moving narratives about the sacrifices of mothers in Islamic history, including the stories of the mothers of the Prophets, the mothers of the Sahabah, and inspiring examples of pious women throughout Islamic civilisation who raised generations of scholars, leaders, and righteous individuals. The book discusses the practical ways in which children can honour their mothers — through respectful speech, attentive care in old age, financial support, making dua for them, and maintaining family ties after their passing. It also addresses contemporary challenges faced by Muslim mothers, balancing modern life with their religious duties, and the importance of creating a nurturing Islamic environment within the home. The Gift of My Mother provides guidance on the Islamic perspective of motherhood as not merely a biological role but as a spiritual mission of the highest order. The book is written in an accessible style that appeals to a broad readership — young adults seeking to strengthen their relationship with their mothers, new mothers looking for inspiration, and anyone who wishes to understand the Islamic framework for family relationships. It makes an excellent gift for Mother's Day, Ramadan, or any occasion where expressing love and gratitude to a mother is appropriate.`,
