    slug: "the-gift-of-ramadan",
    description: `The Gift of Ramadan is a comprehensive and beautifully crafted book that serves as a complete guide to understanding and maximising the benefits of the blessed month of Ramadan. Published by Darussalam and categorised under Ramadan literature, this book covers every significant aspect of the fasting month, making it an essential companion for Muslims who wish to deepen their spiritual experience during this most sacred time of the Islamic calendar. The book provides a thorough explanation of the Fiqh (jurisprudence) of fasting, including the conditions that make fasting obligatory, those who are exempted, the intention (niyyah), things that invalidate the fast, and the rulings on common situations that fasting Muslims encounter. It draws upon the major schools of Islamic jurisprudence while presenting the strongest scholarly opinions with their supporting evidences from the Quran and authentic Sunnah. Beyond the legal aspects, The Gift of Ramadan delves into the spiritual dimensions of fasting, explaining how Ramadan serves as a comprehensive programme for self-purification, increased devotion, and renewed commitment to Allah. The book explores the concept of taqwa (God-consciousness) as the ultimate goal of fasting and provides practical guidance on how to achieve it through Quran recitation, night prayers (Taraweeh and Tahajjud), increased charity, and sincere repentance. Readers will find dedicated chapters on Laylat al-Qadr (the Night of Decree), its virtues, and how to seek it during the last ten nights of Ramadan. The book also covers the etiquette of Iftar and Suhoor, the virtues of feeding fasting people, the recommended acts of worship throughout the month, and the significance of Zakat al-Fitr. The historical context of Ramadan is presented through accounts of how the Prophet (peace be upon him) and his companions observed the month, providing readers with practical models to emulate. The Gift of Ramadan includes guidance on maintaining the momentum of Ramadan's spiritual gains beyond the month itself, ensuring that the lessons learned during fasting are carried forward throughout the year. It is suitable for individuals, families, Islamic schools, and mosque study circles, making it a versatile resource for the entire Muslim community during Ramadan and throughout the year for preparation and reference.`,
