    slug: "the-kindness-of-the-queen",
    description: `The Kindness of the Queen is an engaging and beautifully illustrated Islamic storybook that narrates the remarkable story of Queen Bilqis, the Queen of Sheba, and her journey from worshipping the sun to embracing the true faith of Allah. Published by Darussalam under the General category, this book brings to life one of the most fascinating stories mentioned in the Quran, found in Surah An-Naml (The Ant), and presents it in a manner that is accessible and captivating for readers of all ages. The story follows the events surrounding the historic encounter between Prophet Sulaiman (Solomon), peace be upon him, and Queen Bilqis of the kingdom of Saba (Sheba). Prophet Sulaiman, who was blessed by Allah with sovereignty over jinn, birds, and the wind, received news through his advisor the hoopoe bird about Queen Bilqis and her magnificent kingdom. The book details how Prophet Sulaiman sent a letter inviting the Queen and her people to worship Allah alone and abandon their worship of the sun. The narrative vividly describes Queen Bilqis's wisdom, intelligence, and humility as she consulted her advisors and ultimately decided to travel to meet Prophet Sulaiman rather than confronting him with force. The Kindness of the Queen highlights the queen's remarkable character — her rational thinking, her openness to truth, and her diplomatic approach to handling the situation. The book describes her famous arrival at Prophet Sulaiman's court, where she was asked to identify her throne that had been miraculously transported by one of Sulaiman's knowledgeable companions. Her response demonstrated both keen perception and submission to the truth she witnessed. Ultimately, Queen Bilqis embraced Islam, declaring her faith in Allah, the Lord of the Worlds, and abandoning the sun worship that she and her people had practised. The book emphasises the qualities that made Queen Bilqis a remarkable figure in Islamic history — her wisdom, her search for truth, her humility despite her power and wealth, and her willingness to accept guidance when it was presented with evidence and wisdom. The colourful illustrations throughout the book bring the story to life, depicting the grandeur of the ancient kingdoms, the magnificent throne of Queen Bilqis, and the wondrous abilities bestowed upon Prophet Sulaiman. The Kindness of the Queen is an excellent book for children and young readers, teaching them valuable lessons about truth-seeking, humility, the importance of wise counsel, and the power of da'wah carried out with wisdom and beautiful preaching.`,
